  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.6,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "- [David] Greetings and\nsalutations, oh, you wordsmiths."
      },
      {
        "start": 4.1,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "You who make language\nsimply by thinking it."
      },
      {
        "start": 7.3,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "Oh, you dreamers and schemers."
      },
      {
        "start": 10.5,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "Hi."
      },
      {
        "start": 11.7,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "Too complicated, too wordy, too elaborate?"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.9,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "Perhaps, but I gotta be me."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.9,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "It's a necessity."
      },
      {
        "start": 18.6,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "Can't be a David without\nthe classic David Wordiness."
      },
      {
        "start": 22.0,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "It's a package deal."
      },
      {
        "start": 23.7,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "As you can tell from my\nhaving written them down,"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.0,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "the words in this video are\nelaborate and necessity,"
      },
      {
        "start": 29.4,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "which I shall define in short order."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.9,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "Then we'll do some word origins,"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.1,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "and finally I'll use\nthem both in a sentence."
      },
      {
        "start": 37.2,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "Elaborate, it's an adjective and a verb."
      },
      {
        "start": 40.3,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "As an adjective, it means\ndetailed or complex."
      },
      {
        "start": 43.5,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Like my introduction just now."
      },
      {
        "start": 44.9,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "That was really detailed."
      },
      {
        "start": 47.2,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "As a verb, it means to\nexplain in more detail"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.4,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "and you say it slightly differently."
      },
      {
        "start": 52.1,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "The adjective is elaborate."
      },
      {
        "start": 53.9,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "The verb is elaborate."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.8,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Subtle difference."
      },
      {
        "start": 57.2,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "And necessity is a noun."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.0,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "It means something that\nis required or needed."
      },
      {
        "start": 62.1,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "Word origin time, elaborate\ncomes from ex and labor,"
      },
      {
        "start": 66.2,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "ex meaning out, and labor meaning work."
      },
      {
        "start": 68.9,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "Labor is a standalone word in\nEnglish that also means work."
      },
      {
        "start": 72.5,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "One of those words where the\nletter X disappears from the ex"
      },
      {
        "start": 75.6,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "prefix, where the X is hiding."
      },
      {
        "start": 77.8,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "You see this also in words\nlike eject, to throw out"
      },
      {
        "start": 80.7,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "or erase, to rub or scrape out."
      },
      {
        "start": 83.6,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Why? It's just easier to\nsay erase than \"ex-rase.\""
      },
      {
        "start": 86.9,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "Easier to say eject than \"ex-ject.\""
      },
      {
        "start": 90.3,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "The root labor gives us\nwords like collaborate,"
      },
      {
        "start": 93.2,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "working together or laborious,\na thing that is a lot of work"
      },
      {
        "start": 96.7,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "or takes a lot of work"
      },
      {
        "start": 98.0,
        "duration": 3.2,
